conditions.name: Patient Replacement Condition
conditions.description: Criteria for replacing a discontinued patient.
conditions.text: If patients discontinue from the study before completion of both periods with evaluable primary outcome for any reason, the patient may be replaced. Replacement should not occur beyond 75 patients enrolled.

conditions.name: Safety Review Hold
conditions.description: Study progress is paused for a safety review after a specific number of patients complete Period 2.
conditions.text: Safety data will be reviewed after the first 6 patients (regardless of type of diabetes) are administered LY900018 in Period 2, and the remaining patients will be dosed after confirmation of the safety.

conditions.name: Hypoglycemia Induction Endpoint
conditions.description: The plasma glucose level that triggers the end of insulin infusion.
conditions.text: The insulin infusion will be stopped once the PG level reaches <60 mg/dL.

conditions.name: TE ADA Additional Follow-up Trigger
conditions.description: Condition that triggers an extended follow-up period for immunogenicity.
conditions.text: Patients with TE ADA at follow-up/ED will undergo additional follow-up.

conditions.name: Admission Reschedule Condition
conditions.description: Condition under which a patient's admission to the CRU can be rescheduled.
conditions.text: Admission can be rescheduled if PG level is not 90 to 250 mg/dL on Day 1.

conditions.name: Non-inferiority Declaration Criteria
conditions.description: Statistical criteria for declaring non-inferiority of LY900018.
conditions.text: Non-inferiority of LY900018 will be declared if the upper limit of the 2-sided 95% CI constructed on the difference in percentage (IMG - LY900018) is less than the NIM of 10%.

transitionRules.name: Screening to Treatment Transition
transitionRules.text: Patients will undergo a screening examination within 28 days prior to enrollment. Prior to the study drug administration on Period 1 Day 1, patients will be randomly assigned to a treatment sequence.

transitionRules.name: Discontinuation for Inadvertent Enrollment
transitionRules.text: If the sponsor or investigator identifies a patient who did not meet enrollment criteria and was inadvertently enrolled, a discussion must occur... to determine if the patient may continue in the study.

transitionRules.name: Discontinuation by Investigator
transitionRules.text: The investigator decides that the patient should be discontinued from the study for any reason.

transitionRules.name: Discontinuation by Patient
transitionRules.text: The patient, or legal representative, requests to be withdrawn from the study.

transitionRules.name: Discontinuation for Other Research
transitionRules.text: Enrollment in any other clinical study involving an investigational product or enrollment in any other type of medical research judged not to be scientifically or medically compatible with this study.

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Study Completion
scheduleTimelineExits.description: Patient completes all protocol-required visits, including the final follow-up visit.

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Lost to Follow-up
scheduleTimelineExits.description: A patient will be considered lost to follow-up if he or she repeatedly fails to return for scheduled visits and is unable to be contacted by the study site.

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Full Study Discontinuation for Safety
scheduleTimelineExits.description: Following the review of the safety data from the first 6 patients to complete Period 2 Day 1, the study will be stopped if deemed necessary for patient safety in the opinion of the Investigator and sponsor.

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Patient Withdrawal
scheduleTimelineExits.description: The patient, or legal representative, requests to be withdrawn from the study.

scheduledDecisionInstances.name: Dosing Continuation Decision
scheduledDecisionInstances.description: Decision point after safety review of the first 6 patients in Period 2 to determine if the remaining patients can be dosed.

scheduledDecisionInstances.name: Inadvertent Enrollment Continuation Decision
scheduledDecisionInstances.description: Decision point between investigator and sponsor on whether an inadvertently enrolled patient can continue in the study.
